The paper deals with visual-inertial SLAM, which is a topic in robotics and computer vision. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new initialization method that involves optimization and consensus tests, which are common techniques in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses mathematical models and algorithms to improve the accuracy and robustness of the initialization method, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
